  "texts": [
    "Methods that attempt to remove undesirable knowledge or behaviors from models that have already undergone pre-training (and maybe also fine-tuning) without retraining those models from scratch are called machine unlearning mechanisms.",
    "These mechanisms rely on further fine-tuning, often with adversarial objectives, on the identification of parameters that are correlated with unwanted information and their modification, and on parameter arithmetic.",
    "Sections 4.1 and 4.2 below cover machine unlearning mechanisms of this kind.",
    "These methods offer a wide range of forgetting guarantees, utility levels of the resulting models, and implementation costs.",
    "Prompt engineering."
  ],
